OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1781790495
OL,3,CInquiry into abuse at Muckamore to
OL,4,Cpublish its findings
OL,6,FThe hospital has also been at the
OL,7,Fcentre of the UK's largest-ever police
OL,8,Finvestigation into the alleged abuse
OL,9,Fof vulnerable adults and a number of
OL,10,Fprosecutions are continuing.
OL,12,FThe public inquiry was established by
OL,13,Fformer health minister Robin Swann and
OL,14,Fbegan hearing witness evidence in June
OL,15,F2022.
OL,17,FThe inquiry heard oral evidence from
OL,18,F181 witnesses and 333 statements have
OL,19,Fbeen considered.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/5
